}
},
"name": "Visual Novel Example",
"notes": {
"0467057c-543d-4a47-a30e-3e10951dea4e": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>This is a <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels\"><strong>label</strong></a>. In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels can do more than this; they can also contain <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels\">code</a>. But let's keep it simple for now.</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 9900.0,
"y": 11980.0
},
"137fd37b-86ce-4a02-8e8d-250172a3f0eb": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>The wide image (your scene's background) is an <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/elements#setting-a-cover\"><strong>element cover</strong></a>. To add one, drag an <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/images\"><strong>image asset</strong></a> from the <strong>Assets</strong> section (left sidebar) and drop it into the element.</p>",
"height": 133.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 321.0,
"x": 6720.0,
"y": 12620.0
},
"145815ed-47d6-4eb9-9d58-9b88c47b1816": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Welcome! This tutorial will guide you through creating a <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_novel\"><strong>visual novel</strong></a> in Arcweave.</p><p>For broader Arcweave fundamentals, check out the <strong>Interactive Fiction</strong> example in the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/workspaces/projects#project-templates\">project templates</a>.</p>",
"height": 169.0,
"theme": "pink",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 5200.0,
"y": 11160.0
},
"36b0f4e4-2344-489f-bca7-e7d44ec26c26": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Notice how the audio changes here. The <em>school</em> audio stops and the <em>festival</em> one starts.</p><p>Click on the attached audio assets, to see their settings.</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 9820.0,
"y": 12500.0
},
"39c8d2fd-4e11-4a2d-971b-c972c7771dd0": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Creating a connection is intuitive: drag from any edge of the source element and drop into the target.</p>",
"height": 101.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 6540.0,
"y": 11640.0
},
"3fd33728-d249-4683-a546-30bfcff6e6da": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>The character images are <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/components\"><strong>components</strong></a>. To attach a component, drag it from the <strong>Components</strong> section (also in the left sidebar) into the element.</p><p>To change the attached components' order, simply drag and drop them relative to each other.</p>",
"height": 190.0,
"theme": "pink",
"width": 321.0,
"x": 6700.0,
"y": 12800.0
},
"424bb5db-dd45-417b-bdb7-c4a838760078": {
"autoHeight": false,
"content": "<p>This is your story's starting <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/elements\"><strong>element</strong></a>. Double click it to edit its title or content. (In <em>rich text,</em> too!)</p>",
"height": 101.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 341.0,
"x": 6280.0,
"y": 10980.0
},
"4b662f1d-bdad-47c9-aad0-77cf6c313047": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>This is a <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels\"><strong>label</strong></a>. In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels can do more than this; they can also contain <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels\">code</a>. But let's keep it simple for now.</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 10360.0,
"y": 11140.0
},
"660685e7-83df-4ae2-83a3-856ec15d614e": {
"autoHeight": false,
"content": "<p>Notice the images in the element below.</p>",
"height": 62.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 321.0,
"x": 6820.0,
"y": 10860.0
},
"8fadad9b-50d9-486d-bb86-f4723fdc939d": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>To begin, press the <strong>Play (▶️)</strong> button in the top menu to enter <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-tools/play-mode/overview\"><strong>Play Mode</strong></a>.</p><p>If you’ve played other Arcweave projects before, you’ll already be familiar with Play Mode.</p><p>This project, however, makes use of the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-tools/play-mode/style-editor\"><strong>Style Editor</strong></a> to create the classic visual novel look, instead of relying on Arcweave’s default CSS.</p>",
"height": 247.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 4860.0,
"y": 11160.0
},
"9db8fd48-acc7-44fa-b8d2-430f8b45d78b": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>To change a character's emotion and facial expression, you need to create a new component. </p><p>Set the desired image asset as the new component's cover.</p><p>Notice how this project uses different components for each characters <em>default</em> and <em>smile</em> expression.</p>",
"height": 226.0,
"theme": "pink",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 9480.0,
"y": 10340.0
},
"b36627c6-29f3-4971-980c-a8d45c547f57": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>This is a <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels\"><strong>label</strong></a>. In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels can do more than this; they can also contain <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels\">code</a>. But let's keep it simple for now.</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 8980.0,
"y": 10800.0
},
"d23b9574-b3ae-4ca6-aaec-639879be8009": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>This is a <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/connections\"><strong>connetion</strong></a>. Connect elements to create the flow of your story.</p>",
"height": 101.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 6780.0,
"y": 11020.0
},
"dea777b9-444a-44f6-b5c3-dee7a72e14ca": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Notice how the audio changes here. The <em>school</em> audio stops and the <em>home</em> one starts.</p><p>Click on the attached audio assets, to see their settings.</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "lightBlue",
"width": 301.0,
"x": 10540.0,
"y": 12360.0
},
"e31f8c73-9d3a-43f2-a009-04a569b1c06b": {
"autoHeight": false,
"content": "<p><strong>Image Credits</strong><br>Characters by <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://sutemo.itch.io/\">Sutemo</a></p><p><strong>Music Credits</strong><br>Bg music by <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://authorseo.itch.io/visual-love-bgm-all-in-one-pack\">AuthorSeo</a></p>",
"height": 141.0,
"theme": "pink",
"width": 281.0,
"x": 10060.0,
"y": 10600.0
},
"ef914b97-7f4c-4269-8a6a-3c7c73b20373": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Click on the attached component to <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/components#editing-components\">edit it</a>.</p><p>You can change its name and cover (as well as add <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/attributes\">attributes</a>, but let's leave this for another tutorial).</p>",
"height": 148.0,
"theme": "pink",
"width": 321.0,
"x": 7100.0,
"y": 12660.0
},
"f1bddc47-bc2c-4942-842d-5359ac1fb039": {
"autoHeight": true,
"content": "<p>Add audio to your elements so it plays during Play Mode.</p><p>To do this, drag an <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/audio\"><strong>audio asset</strong></a> from the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/overview\"><strong>Assets</strong></a> section in the left sidebar and drop it into the element.</p><p>Click on the attached audio asset to set its behavior: play once, loop, or stop.</p>",
"height": 205.0,
